documents.commentText:
To Whom It May Concern;

I suffer from several medical ailments that cause chronic pain. In addition to this, I have social anxiety that is debilitating.  So much so that I collect SSDI, much to my dismay.  After trying the pain management route and becoming addicted to these substances and taking about two years to quit entirely, and then using the Methadone Program in the manner in which it was meant to and tapering off of this after about a year.  I had just come to the conclusion that it was my fate to live with chronic pain, I found Kratom.  With this wonderful plant, not only have my pain and anxiety become tolerable, but I actually have hope that if given the chance, and Kratom does not become a Schedule I narcotic, when my Social Security Disability comes up for review in two years or so. that I will be able to return to work and once again become a productive member of society once more.  I cannot stress enough what value that would have for me.

I do, however, have doubts about the Kratom that is sold in "head shops" since they have additives that I am unsure of both the safety and efficacy.  So taking a look at that might be a worthwhile endeavor.
